description: The late monarch was the clear winner of a poll which asked more than 2,000 Brits to vote for their top female role models. Diana, Princess of Wales came in second place, and Mother Teresa was in third.

title: Jerusalem capital decision reversed, Penny Wong announces
description: The Albanese government has reversed its predecessor's decision to recognise Jerusalem as Israel's capital.

title: Liz Truss is 'in office but not in power' amid claims Sunak and Mordaunt will work together
description: Rishi Sunak (pictured), who came second to Liz Truss in the Conservative leadership contest, is said to have spoken to a key Mordaunt backer with a 'tacit' suggestion he could serve as her Chancellor.

title: Royal Family in Australia: King Charles, Prince William, Princess Kate may visit Sydney in 2024
description: King Charles, Prince William and Princess Kate could all visit Australia in 2024 to mark an important milestone for NSW's parliament. It would be the first time in history a King comes Down Under.

title: Quinton Simon's mom Leilani 'admitted to drug use while pregnant'
description: Court documents describe how Leilani Simon, 22, is a 'chronic, unrehabilitated substance abuser of cocaine and cannabis' who allegedly tested positive for cocaine at the birth of one of her three children

title: Kyle Rittenhouse starts YouTube channel devoted to guns and giving 'advice' to likeminded Americans
description: Kyle Rittenhouse, the man who was found not guilty of murder after shooting three people during a protest in Kenosha, Wisconsin, has started a Youtube channel to talk 'about guns.'

title: Fourth 'Green Goblin' gang member hands herself in: Woman, 26, is charged with robbery and let out
description: Dariana Peguero, 26, turned herself in to New York City police on Saturday, only to be let go on supervised released. She is the fourth member of the 'Green Goblin' gang to turn herself in.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: If the Prime Minister is a lame duck, wise Tories must act
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: It promised to usher in a golden era of prosperity for all, rich and poor, with a laser-like focus on igniting the lethargic economy.

title: Britain is set to see its hottest ever year with an Indian summer at Halloween
description: Britain is set for its hottest year on record as an Indian summer spell ahead of Halloween will see temperatures of 21C (70F) amid warm air being blown over from Africa.

title: Just 26% of likely voters think Biden should run for reelection in 2024 and Democrats are split
description: Most voters don't want Biden to run for reelection, another dire poll shows just three weeks before the midterms - and Democrats are split on whether they want to see him as their candidate.

title: Single photo shows dire state of Australian airfares with price of flights to double
description: Australians looking to book a holiday over Christmas could pay almost double for airfares as experts warn skyrocketing prices will remain high for months.

title: Man, 49, arrested for setting NYC Bangladeshi restaurant on FIRE after it botched his order
description: A New York man was arrested after setting fire to a restaurant that had reportedly gotten his order wrong. Choephel Norbu, 49, was arrested Friday after drunkenly setting the restaurant ablaze.
